# Docs style conventions

- Match frontmatter `title` to the page H1 exactly.
- Include intro content after headings; avoid heading-only sections.
- Start with goal-oriented introduction and prerequisite list.
- End with next steps or related resources.
- Use sentence case headings and inline markdown links.
- Use active voice and address the reader as "you".
- Follow Grafana naming conventions (for example `Grafana Cloud`, `OpenTelemetry`, `Kubernetes`).
- Prefer concise, direct wording and complete list-item sentences.

Primary reference:
- `docs/AGENTS.md`
